Lovely anatomy, but I feel like that's not the point. Obviously the author wants us to take something more than just a good nut from this story, otherwise he could just ended it with some ntr. It appears that he means to convey that we as humans try to justify our cruel treatment of sexual objects by dehumanizing them, and by attempting to disassociate from the very real human aspect of them. These are robots, clearly, but when they look and talk like us, it makes the line between evil and indifference blurry.
